# Linux User Management

Linux user management is used by system administrators to manage users and groups in the system.

It allows administrators to:
- Create users
- Modify users
- Delete users
- Assign users to groups
- Manage permissions

---

## Important Files Used in User Management

| File | Description |
|-----|-------------|
| /etc/passwd | Stores user account information |
| /etc/shadow | Stores encrypted passwords |
| /etc/group | Stores group information |

---

## Create User
Command used to create a new user.
sudo useradd devops1
Set Password
Command used to set password for user.
sudo passwd devops1
Create Group
sudo groupadd devops
Add User to Group
sudo usermod -aG devops devops1
Switch User
su - devops1
Delete User
sudo userdel devops1

